    q: "My nugget ice machine is making slush instead of proper nugget. What's wrong?",
    a: "Most likely extrusion mechanism wear. The extrusion mechanism compresses scraped ice into nugget shape before discharge; when it wears, you get slush instead of nugget. Replacement runs $480 to $780. Other possible causes: refrigerant low (leak driving freeze inefficiency), auger speed sensor drift, or scale buildup on the evaporator drum interior. We diagnose in a targeted order rather than guess-and-replace."
  },
