  {
    q: "Why do nugget repairs cost more than cube repairs?",
    a: "Nugget machines have more mechanical wear points. Cube has water flow plus harvest cycle. Flake has auger drive. Nugget has auger drive PLUS extrusion mechanism. More parts equals more potential failures equals higher service cost over machine life. The trade-off is the chewable ice texture that hospitality and healthcare favor."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service hospital nugget machines (Follett medical-grade)?",
